        h1 Modes
        p The Service Portal can be opened in different modes, it will automatically adapt to the given use case. 
        h2 Mode #1 : In context of an Item defined by wsId/dmsId
        p When opening the portal with URL parameters wsId and dmsId pointing to an item record, the portal will retrieve the EBOM of the given item and display its structure. Service technicians can navigate through the BOM, select spare parts and create Spare Parts Requests or Problem Reports in context of the selected item. In this scenario, Spare Parts are determined by the defined property on the EBOM items.
        p See below the example layout of 
            span.code http://localhost:8080/service?wsId=57&amp;dmsId=14669 
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-10.png' style='max-width:640px;')
        a(href='service?wsId=57&dmsId=14669' target='_blank')
        h2 Mode #2 : In context of an Item defined by Part Number
        p Note that the same can be achieved by passing the URL parameter 
            span.code number 
            |followed by an item part number. In this case, the system will retreive the matching item first before then opening the related item's EBOM and viewable.
        p See belw the example layout of 
            span.code http://localhost:8080/service?number=002771 
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-11.png' style='max-width:640px;')
        a(href='service?number=002771' target='_blank')
        h2 Mode #3 : Product Browser 
        p If no wsId and dmsId are provided, the portal will open a landing page showing a catalog of serviceable products. Users can navigate through this catalog, select a product of interest and open its BOM to create Spare Parts Requests or Problem Reports in context of the selected product. The list of products being shown in the landing page can be configured using settings.js. The Spare Parts will be determined by the Product's Service BOM if available - if not, the related EBOM and the defined Spare Part flag attribute will be used.
        p See below the example layout of 
            span.code http://localhost:8080/service 
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-12.png' style='max-width:640px;')
        a(href='service' target='_blank')
        h2 Mode #4 : Asset Browser
        p If no wsId and dmsId are provided and the URL parameter 
            span.code &amp;type=assets 
            |is contained instead, the portal will open a landing page showing an Asset browser as well as assigned Asset Service Tickets. Users can open such a service ticket or an asset directly. In both cases, the asset's Service BOM or Engieering BOM will be used for the viewer, BOM and Spare Parts list generation. This mode requires the installation of the given template from the library for the Asset management.
        p See below the example layout of 
            span.code http://localhost:8080/service?type=assets 
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-13.png' style='max-width:640px;')
        a(href='service?type=assets' target='_blank')
