        h2 Configuring Service BOM Support
        p The following settings are required if the Service Portal should use the related Service BOM for the Spare Parts list creation instead of the Engineering BOM items. These settings must be aligned with the given configuration settings of the Service BOM Editor. Multiple settings must be defined for each major item type in the Service BOM, especially the Type field value (fieldValue). Both groupLabel and icon impact the disply of given BOM entries in the Service Portal. 
        table 
            tr
                th Setting 
                th Default Value 
                th Description  
            tr  
                td serviceBOMTypes.sparePart
                td { fieldValue : 'Spare Parts List', groupLabel : 'Spare Parts', icon : 'icon-package' }
                td This will drive the list of items that can be ordered as single Spare Parts
            tr  
                td serviceBOMTypes.kit
                td { fieldValue : 'Service Kit', groupLabel : 'Kits', icon : 'icon-list' }
                td This will drive the list of items that can only be ordered as part of a Maintenance Kit
            tr  
                td serviceBOMTypes.offering
                td { fieldValue : 'Service Offering', groupLabel : 'Service Offerings', icon : 'icon-layers' }
                td This will drive the list of items that can only be ordered as part of Service Offerings
        h2 Configuring support for Assets  
